            "description": "* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.\n\n* WHERE...A portion of northeast Illinois, including the following\ncounty, Cook.\n\n* WHEN...Until 1245 AM CDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying\nand flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. Streams\ncontinue to rise due to excess runoff from ongoing rainfall.\nExpect many areas of slow moving or standing water.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 352 PM CDT, doppler radar and automated rain gauges\nindicated heavy rain. Flooding is already occurring in the\nwarned area. Between 2 and 5 inches of rain have fallen.\n- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are possible in the\nwarned area over the next one hour.\n- Some locations that will experience flooding include...\nChicago, Elgin, Cicero, Arlington Heights, Evanston,\nSchaumburg, Palatine, Skokie, Des Plaines, Oak Lawn, Berwyn,\nMount Prospect, Hoffman Estates, Oak Park, Glenview, Buffalo\nGrove, Bartlett, Ohare Airport, Streamwood and Hanover Park.\n- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood"

In northeast Illinois, Central\nCook, DuPage, Kane, Kendall, Lake IL, McHenry, Northern Cook,\nNorthern Will and Southern Cook.\n\n* WHEN...Through late tonight.\n\n* IMPACTS...Creeks and streams may rise out of their banks.
